# ~/.zshrc.local — your personal, machine-local zsh tweaks.
#
# kronuzsh sources this file last (if it exists), so it can override anything the
# prompt and integrations set up. To use it, copy this file into place and edit:
#
#   cp <path-to-kronuzsh>/zshrc.local.example ~/.zshrc.local
#
# As shipped it tints the host name and shortens the working-directory path, to show the
# kind of thing you can do; uncomment the rest you want. This is an interactive-shell file
# (sourced near the end of .zshrc), so it's the place for
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_* overrides, zstyles, and tool hooks. It is NOT the place for anything
# that puts a tool on PATH (cargo, ~/.local/bin, pyenv, ...): that has to happen before
# .zshrc runs, or integrations/init.zsh won't detect the tool. Put PATH in ~/.profile
# instead (sourced at login, before .zshrc):
#   [ -r "$HOME/.cargo/env" ] && . "$HOME/.cargo/env"
#   case ":$PATH:" in *":$HOME/.local/bin:"*) ;; *) PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"; export PATH ;; esac

# --- Prompt: tint the host name, to tell machines apart at a glance ---
# The host segment is a neutral silver by default. Colour it per machine so you know
# where you are at a glance (a base-palette name like $col[green], or a raw zsh colour
# %F{N} / %F{#RRGGBB}). A handy convention: green = remote / VM / dev box, blue = your
# local laptop, leave it silver for anything unlabeled (and reserve red for prod). This
# box is a dev box:
PROMPT_KRONUZ_COLOR_HOST='$col[green]'

# --- Prompt: other colours (any semantic name from the colour table in prompt.md) ---
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_COLOR_TIME='%F{45}'
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_COLOR_BRANCH='%B$col[white]'
# The pwd is white, turning red as root. Override the whole colour, reproducing the
# %(!.root.normal) switch if you want to keep a root-distinct colour:
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_COLOR_PWD='%(!.$col[orange].$col[lightsteelblue])'

# --- Prompt: pin a base ANSI colour. Also fixes `dim`'s colours on a terminal whose
# palette can't be queried (e.g. over SSH / Eternal Terminal). #RRGGBB or a 0-255 index.
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_PALETTE_RED='#ff5c57'
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_PALETTE_BLUE='#57c7ff'

# --- Prompt: glyphs ---
# No Nerd Font? Switch to plain-Unicode glyphs (renders in any font):
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_NERD_FONT=0
# Retune or hide ('') one glyph. Names: os branch tag commit remote action clean dirty
# stashed ahead behind staged modified conflicted untracked venv vim emacs jobs duration
# ssh container dot return overwrite caret caret_alt.
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_GLYPH_MODIFIED='*'
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_GLYPH_OS=''            # hide the OS logo next to the hostname

# --- Prompt: behaviour ---
# Shorten the working-directory path: full (default), short (fish-style ~/D/k/i/bat),
# base (just the current directory's name), or absolute ($HOME expanded to its path).
PROMPT_KRONUZ_PWD_STYLE=short
# Show a command's duration once it ran longer than this many seconds (default 3):
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_CMD_DURATION_MIN=5
# Transient prompt: past prompts collapse to the run directory + a caret; '' turns it off.
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_TRANSIENT=''
# Swap just the collapsed caret for an emoji or any string (the rest stays the default):
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_TRANSIENT_CARET='🚀'
# How the whole collapsed line (pwd, caret, command) is restyled: dim (default), mute, keep.
# PROMPT_KRONUZ_TRANSIENT_STYLE=mute

# --- Tool hooks (safe here: PATH is already set up by ~/.profile) ---
# command -v direnv >/dev/null && eval "$(direnv hook zsh)"
# export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"; [[ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ]] && source "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"

# --- Tool config (env only; nothing PATH-related) ---
# ripgrep: a config file with your default flags (smart-case, hidden, ...)
# export RIPGREP_CONFIG_PATH="$HOME/.config/ripgrep/config"
# fzf: tune the pickers
# export FZF_DEFAULT_OPTS='--height 60% --layout=reverse --border --info=inline'
# eza: your own theme dir (default is kronuzsh's bundled Kronuz theme)
# export EZA_CONFIG_DIR="$HOME/.config/eza"
